node.text:
Who wants to see a great product in a review with a twist of fun?

A great alternative to MagSafe Charger that allows you to use your iPhone 12 while placing it still on the desk and charging it at the same time. 

Thanks to @esrgear.fr & @esrgear_official for sending the review unit. 

Full Video is on our YouTube Channel.

#iPhone12 #iPhone12ProMax #fun #iPhone12Pro #iPhone12Mini #Apple #iPhone #MagSafe #MagSafeCharger

Hands-on and review of the charger. 
Charger was used with the iPhone 12 Pro Max. 

Drop a comment and tell us what you think. 

Intro Music: Good World Gone Bad (Wildside Remix by Splasher! licensed to 9TechEleven by Epidemic Sound).

node.text:
Anker Nano is a great Fast Charger for your new iPhone:

• Blazing Fast speeds (20W) - 3X faster than the original 5W iPhone charger
• Ultra Compact Size 
• Lightweight and Portable
• More affordable than the Apple Chargers in most regions
• USB-C port 

@anker_official provided us with a review unit of the Anker Nano - not a paid post

You can get Anker Nano fast Charger for your new iPhone: https://amzn.to/34bTTzE

#iPhone12 #Anker #AnkerNano #ImTheFastest #9TechEleven #iPhone12ProMax #iPhone12Mini #iPhone12Pro

⌚️ Apple Watch Series 7 Will NOT be released in September according to recent information obtained first by Nikkei and corroborated by Bloomberg. 

📆Apple Watch Series 7 is still expected to be announced during Apple’s September Event but the release is expected some time in November.

👨🏻‍💻 Apple is focusing on a new design for the Apple Watch series 7 which will also bring larger models for the first time since the  Watch Series 4. The new Apple Watch Series 7 is expected to be available in 41mm and 45mm, which is slightly larger than the current 40mm and 44mm. 

❤️ No new health features are expected this year. However, Apple is focusing to bring blood pressure measurement in the next generations of the  Watch. 

🛍Are you on planning to purchase a new Apple Watch this year?

node.text:
Apple admitted (!) its mistake with Safari in iOS 15

The new design with the web address bar being placed on the bottom of Safari in the first 5 betas of iOS 15 has been flawed and universally blamed by press and iOS users. 

The biggest issues aren’t related to our past habits. However, the UI elements of many websites are already placed on the bottom of each page making the coexistence with Safari almost unbearable. Banking apps or e-shops have been some of these affected apps. 

Apple listened (well done Apple!!!) and delivered a new option within the Safari settings that allows you to set the url bar either on top or the bottom. 

Where do you think it’s better, top or bottom?

node.text:
Apple has released another round of iOS 15 Beta versions for the iPhone and iPad. 

• iOS 15 Developer Beta 5 
• iPadOS 15 Developer Beta 5 &
• tvOS Developer Beta 5 are out

Apple continues the 2week release cycle for new betas but we will soon start the weekly releases before the final stable release in September. 

Check our post and see what’s new based on what we have found so far. 

Beta versions for public beta testers are soon to be released. 

🔥The location of your Devices connected to Find My network may also will now be updated in real time and not with a considerable lag of some minutes. Need to test this to see how it works and will get back to you. 

What’s your favorite new iOS 15 feature ?

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
